    "updated_at": "2014-05-22T04:28:58Z",
    "body": "Hmm, the patch doesn't seem necessary as I initially thought - I thought `as_utf16_p` should be renamed to `with_utf16_p` and it'd be better if it is available regardless of OS (so added a trait at `c_str`).\nBut I now think there's too small usage of the trait outside of windows, while (re-)implementing `as_utf16_p` is still easy for such cases.\n",
